{"lemma":"عَلِيَّةٍ","slug":"عَلِيَّةٍ","root":"ع.ل.#","root_slug":"ع-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَلِيّ","root":"علو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30139","n30411","n30429"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be exalted, high","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عَلِيَ ٱلْقَمَرُ فِي سَمَاءِ ٱللَّيْلِ","english":"The moon rose up in the night sky."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to excel, to stand out","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عَلِيَ فِي ٱلْمَجْدِ وَٱلْمَكَارِمِ"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"high, tall"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"exalted, lofty, excellent"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Ali"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"ʿAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib, the son-in-law of the Islamic prophet Muhammad through Ali's marriage to the Islamic prophet's daughter, Fāṭimah al-Zahrāʾ, recognized as the Islamic prophet's fourth rightly-guided successor in most of Sunni Islam and as the Islamic prophet's first legitimate successor in Shia Islam"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَلَى (ʕalā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Ultimately from Proto-Semitic *ʕall-, *ʕaly- (“to be high; exalted”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *ʕal-, *ʕVl(ay)- (“to be high, tall; to rise, ascend”).\nCognate with Hebrew עָלָה (ʿalá, “to ascend, rise, grow, develop”), Hebrew עלי (ʿeli, “ascent”) and thereby Eli.\n\nFrom the root ع ل و (ʕ l w) or ع ل ي (ʕ l y)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.li.ja/","/ʕa.lijj/","/ʕalj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30139","headword_ar":"عِلِّيَّةٌ","root":"El","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iy~apN","text_ar":"عُلِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An upper chamber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurofapN","text_ar":"غُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAliY~u","text_ar":"عَلَالِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.) [It is mentioned also in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~api qawomihi","text_ar":"عِلِّيَّةِ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iy~atihimo","text_ar":"عُلِّيَّتِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [both mistranscribed in the CK,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiloyatihimo","text_ar":"عِلْيَتِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed, [which belongs to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~ihimo","text_ar":"عِلِّيِّهِمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iy~ihimo","text_ar":"عُلِّيِّهِمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which are also mistranscribed in the CK,] mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of the exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated, of his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b3-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~uwna","text_ar":"عِلِّيُّونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in the Kur [lxxxiii. 18 and 19] is [said to be] a pl. of which the sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iY~N","text_ar":"عِلِّىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~apN","text_ar":"عِلِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iy~apN","text_ar":"عُلِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or a pl. having no sing., (K, TA,) [or rather it is from the Hebr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"עֶלְיוֹן","text_ar":"עֶלְיוֹן","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ high, ” or “ higher, ”] and is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place in the Seventh Heaven, to which ascend the souls of the believers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most elevated of the Paradises;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sij~iyn","text_ar":"سِجِّين"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the most elevated of the places of the fires [of Hell]: or rather it is properly a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the inhabitants thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for this [sort of] pl. is peculiar to rational beings: (TA:) it is mentioned again in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which see other explanations]. (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30411","headword_ar":"عِلْيَةٌ","root":"Elw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliY~N","text_ar":"عَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of which it is said to be pl.]."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30429","headword_ar":"عُلِّيَّةٌ","root":"Elw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) with damm, (Msb, K,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is meksoorah, being with teshdeed, as is also the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~iylapN","text_ar":"فُعِّيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~iyqapN","text_ar":"مُرِّيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~iyqN","text_ar":"مُرِّيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iywapN","text_ar":"عُلِّيوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealawotu","text_ar":"عَلَوْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~apN","text_ar":"عِلِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (S, Msb, K,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiE~iylapN","text_ar":"فِعِّيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, as some say, from a reduplicate root, and of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEoliy~apN","text_ar":"فُعْلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; adding that there is no instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~iylapN","text_ar":"فُعِّيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the language; (S;) [therefore it is also mentioned in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El","text_ar":"عل"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An upper chamber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chamber in the upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurofapN","text_ar":"غُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAliY~u","text_ar":"عَلَالِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~iy~apN","text_ar":"عِلِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said, may signify also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"board upon which is placed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEoyaAr","text_ar":"مِعْيَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assay-balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 550.) ―         -b3-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}